### Resources

#### Nova

You can run Nova by cloning [the `nova` branch of Telescope](https://github.com/TelescopeJS/Telescope/tree/nova).

The files I work on in the video are [`demo-app.jsx`](https://github.com/TelescopeJS/Telescope/blob/nova/packages/nova-demo/demo-app.jsx) and [`demo-component.jsx`](https://github.com/TelescopeJS/Telescope/blob/nova/packages/nova-demo/demo-component.jsx).

#### Packages

The features I show in the video have all been extracted as separate, open-source packages:

- [React List Container](https://github.com/meteor-utilities/react-list-container): used to subscribe to a publication, and then pass on the resulting documents to a child component.
- [React Form Containers](https://github.com/meteor-utilities/React-Form-Containers): used to display simple new document and edit document forms.
- [Smart Publications](https://github.com/meteor-utilities/smart-publications): used to automatically set up publications.
- [Smart Methods](https://github.com/meteor-utilities/smart-methods): used to automatically set up methods. 

